-- German Diesel, Heating Oil Use Rose in January, Industry Says
-- B y   K o n s t a n t i n   R o z h n o v
-- 2013-04-03T14:46:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-03/german-diesel-heating-oil-use-rose-in-january-industry-says.html
Germany ’s diesel and heating oil
consumption rose in January from a year earlier, according to
 data  from the Association of the German Petroleum Industry.  Diesel use in  Europe ’s largest economy gained 2.4 percent
to 2.5 million tons, data posted today on the association’s
website show.  Heating oil demand rose 26 percent to 1.68 million tons.
Germany is the continent’s largest market for that fuel.  Gasoline consumption declined 7.6 percent to 1.38 million
tons, the data show. European nations have shifted to greater
use of diesel, at the expense of gasoline, in the past decade.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Konstantin Rozhnov in London at 
 krozhnov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
